# Chamber
  `entered_chamber := true`
  > The bell chamber is round, dry, and impossibly deep beneath the ruined tower.
  > A cracked silver bell hangs from three chains over a black pool.
  > `chalk_circle` A chalk ring glows faintly at the pool's edge.
  + Inspect the bell -> [.Bell]
  + Study the pool -> [.Pool]
  + Climb back to the courtyard -> [Courtyard]("/ruins.saga")

## Bell
  > The bell has no tongue. Its inner curve is scratched with names you almost recognize.
  > `bronze_tongue` The bronze tongue hums softly in your pack.
  + Fit the bronze tongue into place -> `bronze_tongue` [.Restore]
  + Touch the scratched names -> [.Names]
  + Step away -> [Chamber]

### Restore
  `bell_restored := true`
  > The bronze tongue rises from your hand and locks itself inside the bell.
  + Ring the bell *-> `trust_blue_scarf` [..TrueRing]
  + Ring the bell anyway -> [..FalseRing]
  + Wait and listen -> [..Names]

### TrueRing
  `bell_rang_true := true`
  > The bell rings without sound. The black pool becomes a sky full of dawn.
  -> [Dawn]("/ending.saga")

### FalseRing
  `bell_rang_false := true`
  > The bell screams. Every chain in the chamber snaps tight, then slackens.
  -> [Return]("/ending.saga")

### Names
  `name_glimpse = rand(3)`
  > Your name is there, but the letters keep changing order.
  *-> `name_glimpse == 0` [.HiddenName]
  -> [..]

#### HiddenName
  `saw_hidden_name := true`
  > For one breath, the letters spell a name that is not yours, but answers when you think it.
  -> [..]

## Pool
  > The pool reflects the chamber as it was: whole, full of candlelight, crowded with silent villagers.
  > `pool_offering` A stranger in the reflection turns your coin over in their fingers.
  + Drop a coin into the pool -> `coin >= 1` [.Offering]
  + Draw a chalk circle at the pool's edge -> `found_chalk` [.Circle]
  + Return to the bell -> [..Bell]

### Offering
  `coin := coin - 1`
  `pool_offering := true`
  > The coin falls upward through the reflection and lands in someone else's palm.
  -> [..]

### Circle
  `chalk_circle := true`
  > The chalk line closes itself into a perfect ring. The pool grows still.
  -> [..]
